<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>ADIF MCP — eQSL Adapter</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>

<body>
  <div class="container">
    <header class="card">
      <div class="site-title">
        <span class="badge">ADIF MCP</span> eQSL Adapter
      </div>
      <nav class="topnav">
        <a href="https://adif-mcp.com">Core</a>
        <a href="https://lotw.adif-mcp.com">LoTW Adapter</a>
        <a href="https://eqsl.adif-mcp.com">eQSL Adapter</a>
        <a href="https://github.com/KI7MT/adif-mcp-eqsl">GitHub</a>
      </nav>
    </header>

    <main>
      <section class="card">
        <h1>eQSL Adapter</h1>
        <p>
          <strong>adif-mcp-eqsl</strong> connects ADIF MCP with
          <a href="https://www.eqsl.cc/">eQSL.cc</a>, making inbound confirmations and inbox sync
          available as typed MCP tools. Upload support is planned for a later milestone.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="card">
        <h2>Features</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Fetch and parse eQSL inbox messages</li>
          <li>Check confirmation statuses</li>
          <li>Normalize eQSL-specific fields to ADIF</li>
          <li>Consistent API with LoTW adapter</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="card">
        <h2>Roadmap</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>M1 — Inbox fetch + confirmation status</li>
          <li>M2 — Normalization and schema alignment</li>
          <li>M3 — Upload support (optional)</li>
        </ul>
      </section>
    </main>

    <footer class="footer">
      © 2025 ADIF MCP Project · MIT License
    </footer>
  </div>
</body>

</html>
